# Frontend Auth

## Token storage

- `sessionStorage` key `template_auth_token`
- `authToken.ts` syncs token for `httpClient` Authorization header
- Store: `stores/auth.ts` — `login`, `register`, `fetchUser`, `hydrate`, `logout`

## Router guards

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — meta-driven (router/index.ts)
meta: { requiresAuth: true }  // redirect to login
meta: { guest: true }          // redirect authenticated users away
```

`beforeEach`: unauthenticated → `login?redirect=`; guest routes when logged in → `home`.

## Views

- `LoginView.vue` / `RegisterView.vue` call `useAuthStore()`
- Show `auth.error`; disable submit while `auth.loading`

## API contract

```typescript
// AuthResponse: { accessToken, expiresAt }
await authApi.login({ email, password })
await authApi.me() // requires Bearer token
```

## Hydration

Call `auth.hydrate()` on app boot (`main.ts`) to restore session and load user.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — storing JWT only in Pinia without sessionStorage sync
// ✅ GOOD — setToken updates sessionStorage + authToken helper
```
